Text: What you think about the implant that goes into the upper arm??
Message JSON: {"userId":"92a8f6f4-8032-4293-b78f-9ce383b69394","text":"What you think about the implant that goes into the upper arm?? "}

Text: The implant is a type of birth control that goes into your upper arm to prevent pregnancy. It used to be called Implanon but now it’s called Nexplanon. It’s a teeny rod that releases progestin to stop ovulation (no egg, no baby) and thickens mucus in your cervix.

Text: Do you get period on the birth control implant
Message JSON: {"userId":"92a8f6f4-8032-4293-b78f-9ce383b69394","text":"Do you get period on the birth control implant"}

Text: Not getting your period sounds crazy right? But, when you’re on birth control, it’s normal and totally ok - especially for the really effective types like the IUD or the implant. And even if you’re on other types of birth control like the pill, patch, or ring, you can skip your period by just starting your new birth control the week of your period instead of taking the placebo pills.
